"{\"uid\": \"nbcchicago.com-paris-2024-summer-olympics-who-is-competing-in-the-womens-uneven-bars-heres-the-lineup-3511106\", \"text\": \"2020 Olympic all-around champion Suni Lee dazzled on the uneven bars on her way to claiming bronze in the women's individual all-around final in Paris.  Suni Leewill take the spotlight for Team USA come Sunday as she competes in the women's uneven bars at the2024 Paris Olympics,three years after taking bronze in that event at the Tokyo Games.  After helpingBiles and the U.S. women win team goldandtaking bronze in the all-aroundcompetition in Paris, Lee's best chance at another medal comes in the uneven bars -- an event where she will be the only American participating.  Stream NBC 5 for free, 24/7, wherever you are.  Lee will face fierce competition, including from Algeria's Kaylia Nemour,\\u00a0who burst onto the scene during the team qualifications, and earned a spot both in the uneven bars competition and in the women's all-around event. Nemour qualified for first place in uneven bars, followed by Qiyuan Qiu and Lee.  Curious about the full lineup? Find it below.  The women's uneven bar finals will take place at 8 a.m. CT on Sunday.  Watch all the action from the Paris Olympic and Paralympic Games live on Peacock  For a full schedule of what to\\u00a0watch\\u00a0and which\\u00a0channel\\u00a0each event will air or\\u00a0stream\\u00a0on, clickhere.\"}"